"{\"uid\": \"messengernews.net-news-news-brief-2024-08-fd-is-tops-in-special-olympics-donations\", \"text\": \"Aug 24, 2024  Fort Dodge won the gold medal in the recent Special Olympics Iowa Cop on a Rooftop fundraiser.  The city Police Department was recently informed that Fort Dodge was the No. 1 fundraising location in Iowa this year.  Area residents donated $3,137.02 to Special Olympics Iowa during the Aug. 16 event at Dunkin', 2520 Fifth Ave. S.  Personnel from the Fort Dodge Police Department, Webster County Sheriff's Office and the Fort Dodge Correctional Facility were at the shop from 6 a.m. to noon that day to collect the donations. Donors received coupons for doughnuts and coffee.Those who gave $20 or more received a tumbler with a Special Olympics Iowa logo.  This is the fourth year Fort Dodge generated the most donations during the annual event. The community previously led the way in donations in 2016, 2017 and 2022.  Statewide more than $33,000 was raised during the Cop on a Rooftop event this year.  The St. Edmond craft and vendor show is 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. on Dec. 6, at St. Edmond High School, 2220 Fourth Ave. N. ...  LAURENS - The Laurens United Methodist Women will hold their annual holiday event from 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. Saturday ...  WEBSTER CITY \\u00ad- Kendall Young Library, Webster City, will be having adult programs throughout the month of ...  WEBSTER CITY - Kendall Young Library, Webster City, will close at 3 p.m. on Nov. 26 and remained closed through ...  The Blanden Memorial Art Museum presents \\\"Walking In Traffic,\\\" a solo exhibition by textile artist Debra Smith, ...  WEBSTER CITY - Kendall Young Library, Webster City, children's department will be having a variety of events in ...    Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Ogden Newspapers of Iowa, LLC | https://www.messengernews.net | 713 Central Ave., Fort Dodge, IA 50501 | 515-573-2141\"}"